==English==

===Etymology===
From ''incohativus'', a participle stem of the Latin word, ''incohare'', "to begin.''

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Describing the initial stage of an act.
# Pertaining to the nature of commencement or beginnings.
# Denoting the start of an action. (Grammatical)

